ai.legendary

Class DictionaryAccess

  • java.lang.Object
    • ai.legendary.DictionaryAccess

  • public class DictionaryAccess
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides various methods for accessing the dictionary and paraphrasing using the dictionary. When the class is initialized it loads everything into HashMaps, so try to only initialize it once.
    Version:
    8/10/2017
    Author:
    ToddSandberg

      • fromLightVerb

        public java.lang.String fromLightVerb(java.lang.String s)

        Returns:

      • fromLightVerb

        public java.lang.String fromLightVerb(java.lang.String subj,
                                      java.lang.String lightverb,
                                      java.lang.String actionverb,
                                      java.lang.String directobj)
        Paraphrases light verb phrases using sentence components. If one of the params are not necessary just put ""
        Parameters:
        subj - = subject of sentence "*I* gave him a bath"
        lightverb - = the light verb used in the sentence "I *gave* him a bath"
        actionverb - = the verb or noun to be verb used in the sentence "I gave him a *bath*"
        directobj - = the direct object of the light verb phrase "I gave *him* a bath"
        Returns:
        paraphrased light verb phrase

        Returns:

      • toLightVerb

        public java.lang.String toLightVerb(java.lang.String subj,
                                    java.lang.String actionverb,
                                    java.lang.String obj)
        paraphrase to a light verb sentence using sentence components. If a field is not used input "" for it.
        Parameters:
        subj - = the subject of the sentence "*I* bathed him"
        actionverb - = the verb of the sentence "I *bathed* him"
        obj - = the object of the sentence "I bathed *him*"
        Returns:
        the paraphrased light verb sentence
